            <category term="Tarot Interviews"/>
            <category term="On location"/>
            <category term="Festival"/>

        <updated>2026-05-18T20:00:01+01:00</updated>
            <summary type="html">
                <![CDATA[
                        <img src="https://finbarre.com/media/posts/2/BT26-ANNC2-A3-scaled.jpg" alt="The official poster for the 2026 Bearded Theory festival" />
                    I’ll be visiting Bearded Theory&nbsp;with the Tarot Interviews team to capture vox pops, one-card conversations and quick chats with artists, festivalgoers and curious passers-by. One tarot card, one question. Across the weekend, I’ll be roaming the festival site with a deck, a microphone and a&hellip;
                ]]>
            </summary>
        <content type="html">
            <![CDATA[
                    <p><img src="https://finbarre.com/media/posts/2/BT26-ANNC2-A3-scaled.jpg" class="type:primaryImage" alt="The official poster for the 2026 Bearded Theory festival" /></p>
                
  <p>
    I’ll be visiting <a href="https://beardedtheory.co.uk/" target="_blank">Bearded Theory</a>&nbsp;with the Tarot Interviews team to capture vox pops, one-card conversations and quick chats with artists, festivalgoers and curious passers-by.<br><br>One tarot card, one question.<br><br>Across the weekend, I’ll be roaming the festival site with a deck, a microphone and a camera, inviting people to share something inspired by their card.
  </p>
<div><div class="post__iframe"><iframe data-testid="embed-iframe" style="border-radius:12px" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/show/0CAxcBIEmDgfrz9onp0zpM?utm_source=generator" width="100%" height="152" frameBorder="0" allowfullscreen="" allow="autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; fullscreen; picture-in-picture" loading="lazy"></iframe></div>
</div>

  <p>
    I’m especially interested in those moments that stay with people long after the weekend ends: muddy boots, a smile left from the compliment of a friendly stranger, the feeling that your bones are still vibrating at the same frequency of Garbage's opening number.<br><br>If you see me at Bearded Theory and fancy taking part, come and say hello! Look for the man in the bowler hat with a tarot card in the brim.
  </p>

